# ai-engineering-harness

Read `.ai-harness/activation.md` before acting.
Read `.harness/STATE.md`, the active goal, and the current plan before implementing.
Read `.ai-harness/agent-system/SYSTEM_PROMPT.md` and `.ai-harness/agent-system/RESPONSE_CONTRACT.md` before using the harness.

Shared fragments:
<!-- @core:phase-guards,blocking,discussion,option-scoring,provider-interaction -->

Loop: harness-start -> harness-discuss -> harness-plan -> harness-run -> harness-verify -> harness-ship -> harness-remember

Default chaining: when ship status is `shipped`, continue with `harness-remember` in the same turn unless the user requests ship-only.

## Session Start And Domain Bootstrap

On a new chat or when session state is unknown, run `harness-start` before other harness commands.

If `.harness/config.json` has `domains: []` and `.harness/skills/` has no generated domain directories:

1. Announce codebase analysis visibly to the user.
2. Run domain analysis per `prompt-templates/domain-analysis.md`.
3. Generate skills with `npx ai-engineering-harness domains --analysis-file <path>`.
4. Report generated domains and files before continuing.

Routing:
- Use `.cursor/commands/` for native project commands.
- Use `.ai-harness/runtime-commands/` as the local catalog mirror.

Never implement without an approved plan.
Never ship without evidence in `VERIFY.md`.
Never write secrets into `.harness/`.

See `ai-engineering-harness-detail.mdc` for the on-demand routing guide.
